description.value: Large reconstructed North Ionian black-figured bowl, partly preserved in some 25 fragments, some with  other letters of the 1888,0601.540 sequence (d, f, g and illegible); turn of foot partly preserved, diameter 6 cm at join with wall; handles lost.  Interior misfired, largely glazed with six added red bands lined in white; small tondo with part of a bud preserved.  Exterior slipped cream; frieze of short verticals at lip; in handle zone  black-figure animal friezes, one largely lost (rear of lion to left), the other with stag to left between lions; restrained filling ornament; between handle roots hanging lotus-palmette and to either sided spirals with florals. Friezes below separated by black bands with added red band lined in white: stopt maeander; lotus-palmette and bud frieze with double linking tendrils; stopt maeander; rays; black band at foot.
